Reading the book and checking this version, it seems like the condition is only based on the current amount, not on the final possible amount. To clarify: 
```javascript
const ACCESSORY_PRICE = 9.99;

var bank_balance = 200.00;
var amount = 99.99;

amount = amount * 2;

// can we afford the extra purchase?
if ( amount  < bank_balance ) { // 199.98 < 200.00 === true!
	console.log( "I'll take the accessory!" );
	amount = amount + ACCESSORY_PRICE; 209.97 < 200 === false!!!
}
// otherwise:
else {
	console.log( "No, thanks." );
}
```

That's why should be:
```javascript
if ( amount + ACCESSORY_PRICE  < bank_balance ) { // 209.97 < 200.00 === false, go to else
	console.log( "I'll take the accessory!" );
	amount = amount + ACCESSORY_PRICE; 
} else ...
```

